(943, 1, '2023-01-22 11:30:32', '2023-01-22 11:30:32', 'It’s time to go back to New Zealand, shall we? And today I will maybe share the most clichée New Zealand experience with you – or shall I rather say Middle Earth experience? Now all of New Zealand truly feels like Middle Earth with its untouched nature, vast landscapes and rugged mountains. But there is one village that takes you right into the ‘Lord of the Rings’ – the cute little Hobbiton.\n<blockquote>It’s time to go back to New Zealand, shall we? And today I will maybe share the most clichée New Zealand experience with you – or shall I rather say Middle Earth experience?</blockquote>\n<ul>\n 	<li>It’s time to go back to New Zealand, shall we?</li>\n 	<li>It’s time to go back to New Zealand, shall we?</li>\n</ul>', 'VueJS Installation and Setup', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '145-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-01-22 11:30:32', '2023-01-22 11:30:32', '', 145, 'http://localhost/coder/?p=943', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(945, 1, '2023-01-22 12:09:38', '2023-01-22 12:09:38', 'Assumption:\nNode and NPM installed into your System\n\nNow you can install VueJS with the following 5 steps.\n<blockquote>Steps</blockquote>\n<ol>\n 	<li>Install Vue Cli globally by typing following command to your Powershell\n\nnpm install -g @vue/cli</li>\n 	<li>Create project named vuejs with the following command\n\nvue create vuejs</li>\n 	<li>Choose options default babel 3 and npm press enter</li>\n 	<li>Run your vuejs application with the following command\n\nnpm run serve</li>\n 	<li>You will see the following message\n\nApp running at:\n- Local: http://localhost:8080/\n- Network: http://192.168.29.56:8080/\n\nNote that the development build is not optimized.\nTo create a production build, run npm run build.\n\nOpen URL http://localhost:8080/ to see your application.</li>\n</ol>', 'VueJS Installation and Setup', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '145-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-01-22 12:09:38', '2023-01-22 12:09:38', '', 145, 'http://localhost/coder/?p=945', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
